Arsenal goalkeeper Wojciech Szczesny has lost his place in the side in recent weeks

Szczesny has not featured for Arsene Wenger's side since the New Year's Day defeat by Southampton

David Ospina has started the last three Arsenal games without conceding a goal

Szczesny's future has been thrown into huge doubt in recent weeks after losing his place to David Ospina following a loss of form and his smoking shame at Southampton on New Years Day. 

The Pole is unlikely to accept spending a season on the bench and the arrival of a new keeper ahead of the next campaign could signal his departure from the Emirates Stadium.

Speaking on Thursday, Wenger refused to confirm whether Szczesny or Ospina will at against Brighton on Sunday.

Wenger regularly plays his second choice goalkeeper in the FA Cup and the manager's team selection on Sunday could provide a major clue towards Szczesny's long term future at the club.

 

